## What is Configra?

Configra is the **tier-2 configuration substrate** for Phenotype projects.
It provides consistent management of settings, feature flags, secrets, and
version information, with local-first persistence, team-collaboration
support, audit trails, and CLI-first workflows.

## Workspace at a glance

| Crate | Concern |
| --- | --- |
| `pheno-config` | Typed runtime `Config` + `ConfigBuilder` (env cascade, TOML+env overlay, `combine()`) |
| `settly` | Settings lifecycle — validation, migration, versioning |
| `config-schema` | JSON schema validation primitives (`SchemaField`, `ConfigSchema`, `SchemaError`) |
| `phenotype-config-loader` | Generic JSON/TOML file loaders (`load_json<T>`, `load_toml<T>`, `ConfigLoadError`) |

See [Getting Started](/getting-started) to clone, build, and run the
workspace locally.

## Quick example

```bash
# Clone and build the workspace
git clone https://github.com/KooshaPari/Configra.git
cd Configra
cargo build --workspace

# Run the full test suite
cargo test --workspace
```

